    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I want to delay in the initial search until I have the map bounds available\r\n\r\nCan you detail this, does it means you want, on first load, to delay instantiation of instantsearch.js interface to when you have the map initialised?\r\n\r\n> Use-case is a widget that plots pins on a map. I want to delay in the initial search until I have the map bounds available.\r\n\r\nThis should be solved at your custom widget level:\r\n\r\n- map.start()\r\n- map.isReady => false\r\n- search.start()\r\n- map.isReady => false\r\n- first results are coming\r\n- custom widget renders\r\n- map.isReady => false\r\n- map.whenReady => plot results\r\n\r\nSo you own widget should be responsible for waiting for the map to be ready, which would mean plotting only when everything is ready. I think this is feasible but will require a bit of work on your side, what do you think?",
