    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Can you detail this, does it means you want, on first load, to delay instantiation of instantsearch.js interface to when you have the map initialised?\r\n\r\nYour example makes sense, except for the fact that my map is rendered and initialized via my widget itself, so I'm not sure how I could init/render the widget without performing that initial search. Note that I can do this via `options.searchFunction`, but I think what I'm lobbying for is a way for a widget to control a similar option, so that I might prevent an initial search from my widget rather than the Instantsearch instance.",
